## Skipping Tests

To tell the verifier *skip* tests in a file `path/to/file.verse` you can
create a file `path/to/file.verse.skip` and add to it lines like:

```
skip(                 fail, "misparsed"){"f(g():any):=g[]; f(g():=6)"}
skip("optional-name", fail, "some other reason"){"f(x:int)<decides>:=x=3, f[x:int]"}
```

So each line is of the form

```
skip(<optional-name-in-quotes>, pass|fail, "the-reason-it-is-skipped-in-quotes") { "exact code for test" }
```

These tests will then be "skipped" when running